718510f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 94th Street
718510f-a.text:

718511f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 94th Street
718511f-a.text:
(1)
Central Park West, west side, north from 94th Street. In the
background at the S.W. corner of 96th Stroet is the Scotch
Presbyterian Chuch, and beyond it, on the N.W. corner is the
First Church of Christ Scientist.
Note the torn-up condition of the street, due to construction
work on the Eighth Avenue subway.
May 31, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, three months later, showing the work of demolition in
process. ''The Towers,'' on the N.W. corner of 94th Street, is
the last building to go. A sixteen-story apartment building
will occupy this entire block, and two more will rise in the
next block, one at 3 West 95th Street and one on the site of
the Scotch Presbyterian Church.
September 10, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPROEUCTIONS.
